Hanjin, Kia Motors, Korea Zinc: South Korea Stocks Preview

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-04-21T23:28:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-21/hanjin-kia-motors-korea-zinc-south-korea-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise. The  Kospi Index (KOSPI)  rose 28.63, or 1.3 percent, to
2,198.54, a record.  Hanjin Shipping Co. (117930 KS): South Korea’s largest
shipping company said a container vessel that was attacked by
pirates near the Gulf of Aden has been rescued and all its crew
are safe, according to a statement. There was “some damage”
done to the ship by the pirates who were not found after the
rescue by the warship Choi Young. The stock fell 1.6 percent to
30,050 won.  Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  (000270 KS): The company plans to begin
building Optima sedans at a U.S. plant in  Georgia , adding about
1,000 workers, as the South Korean automaker aims to boost sales
in the market to a record this year. Production of the midsize
car will start in late 2011 at the  West Point , Georgia, factory,
Tom Loveless, the company’s vice president for U.S. sales, said
at the New York International Auto Show. The stock gained 0.8
percent to 77,300 won.  Korea Zinc Co. (010130 KS): Gold rose to a record for the
fifth straight session, settling above $1,500 an ounce for the
first time. Silver rose above $46 an ounce. Korea Zinc, which
produces gold and silver, climbed 3.8 percent to 478,500 won.  Samsung Electronics Co. (005930 KS): The company will
acquire a 15 percent stake in a TCL Corp. unit, TCL said in a
statement to the Shenzhen Stock Exchange. The unit will start to
produce Samsung’s liquid crystal display panels from August, TCL
said in a separate statement to the exchange.  Asia ’s biggest
maker of chips, flat screens and mobile phones added 1.3 percent
to 928,000 won.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
 sshin15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
